ğŸ§© What is IAM?
IAM in GCP lets you control who can access what resources and how.
Every service account, user, or group should get just enough access â€” nothing more, nothing less.
This is called the principle of least privilege.
âš™ï¸ Example: Service Account for Dataflow
Instead of using your personal account,
create a dedicated service account for Dataflow with only the required roles ğŸ‘‡
Copy code
Bash
gcloud iam service-accounts create dataflow-sa \
 --display-name="Dataflow Service Account"

gcloud projects add-iam-policy-binding my-project \
 --member="serviceAccount:dataflow-sa@my-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com" \
 --role="roles/dataflow.worker"

gcloud projects add-iam-policy-binding my-project \
 --member="serviceAccount:dataflow-sa@my-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com" \
 --role="roles/storage.objectViewer"
